rComments: 1 of my fave courses in undergrad. lec were so very enjoyable(had a hard time letting go of prospects of microbio in grad school after taking his class) def makes u work for it but what the heck else are you pursuing an Honours BSc for? If you enjoy real learning and want to witness the crazy world where microlife meets macro environment,do it!
He is a very very very hard teacher. His slides are basically useless. You must record his lectures if you want a surviving chance in his class.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Lecture heavy', 'Tough grader']

rComments: One of my favourite profs at UTM. He is great at teaching, tests are very fair and is available for help outside of class. I had a great experience overall and I've learned a great deal of material in this class.

Easily one of the best profs I've had. Super friendly, very approachable, and really knows his stuff. Tests are very fair if you are responsible and keep up with the material. If you ever get confused or feel that he goes to fast, ask to clarify after class, it usually helps a lot for tests.

By far the best Bio course I've took in the past four years. Dr. Short displayed genuine  attention towards the well being of his students, as well excitement and dedication for the material and its preparation. This reciprocity of effort was refreshing. If you truly like the material and pay attention, you'll do well.

Fantastic prof! Lectures were very clear-cut and he was always willing to answer questions. He even agreed to meet me early morning to explain an online assignment that I couldn't get to work. Super approachable and remembers you if you've talked to him in the past! Makes you feel like your understanding matters to him unlike some other bio profs.
he was alright. just do past tests and youre good to go

Professor Short repeated most questions from past tests and when he didn't, the questions were still similar to past tests. The average going into the final was a high 70, and at the end it was a low 70. Know  your stuff inside out and you'll do great in the course, even with the brutal final exam :)
one of my best prof, easy labs, helpful TAs, and easy exams (only do past papers since he repeats questions every year)

ok prof, not that great at explaining stuff but most material can be learned from online videos. prof not really approachable (RARELY stayed for office hours) and TAs aren't that helpful either. If you have Farheen as a TA, AVOID her...she has NO idea what is going on in labs!

Lectures were meh, but labs were fun to do and helpful. In terms of difficulty, it should not be too hard to get good lab marks. Term tests ask for stupidly nitty gritty details, and the "some of the above" options leave you wondering how well you did. Only spent half a day studying for the exam and ended up with a marker higher than going in (A-)

So dreamy! And very enthusiastic about the course. The key to doing well is to attend lectures and review often as he moves VERY fast in class. Make sure to ask him to clarify concepts as his tests are VERY specific (AKA, minute details in a random table that you probably didn't think would be tested on). You seriously cannot slack in this course!

Decent prof & nice guy but his courses are messy. He speaks fast so  record the lectures and is sometimes unclear. His slides can be confusing and the info is too broad for undergrad. His tests suck because the MC involves all/some/none of the above and short answer is marked hard. Decent but not great prof and only take his courses if you have to.

He is perfect. As people said, very dreamy. He explains concepts very clearly (maybe a bit fast for my liking... you really have to pay attention). He will repeat concepts that are important for the term tests. He loves helping if you're having trouble with the course or just want to chat. Overall a very good experience and interesting course.
Very delightful professor, teaches well, and looks super dreamy when in front.

Went into the exam with a 92. came out with a 79. know everything in n out for the final. he tries to make challenging during the semester. most end up doing well. but then the makes final so hard to get the exact grade that they want him to submit to the office. Not fair for a course that doesnt use any textbook. topics too broad for a 1/2yr cours

Came into exam with a high B+ (borderline A-), thought the exam was fair, doable and only struggled on one or two questions. Somehow ended up in the course with a mid B. The bell curving down in this course is so obvious and is not an accurate reflection of one's performance in the course. Otherwise, he injects some interest in the course.
Absolutely AMAIZING Prof! He teaches well, has a great sense of humor, very FAIR...and on top of that he is extremly goood looking:D Too bad he is married ;)
